  "body": "This issue outlines the new DB getters I have in mind, this will enable better state gen management UX and more efficient usage around state.\r\n\r\n1- \r\n`LastSavedState(ctx) (state, error)`\r\nThis returns the last saved state (ie highest slot) in the DB. Given current slot is at 100 but the available state in DB is slot 90. It returns state at slot 90\r\n2- \r\n`LastSavedStateBeforeSlot(ctx, slot uint64) (state, error)`\r\nThis returns the last saved state that's before input slot in the DB. Given current slot is at 100 the available state is slot 90, but the input slot is 80, it returns the last saved state before 80\r\n3-\r\n`LastSavedBlock(ctx) (block, error)`\r\nSame as (1), this returns the last saved block (ie highest slot) in the DB\r\n4-\r\n`LastSavedBlockBeforeSlot(ctx, slot uint64) (block, error)`\r\nSame as (4), this returns the last saved block (highest slot) that's before input slot in the DB\r\n",
